The paper discusses the problem of approximate string matching, which is a common problem in several areas of computer science such as computational biology, text processing, and pattern recognition. The algorithm presented in the paper is output-sensitive and improves existing theoretical bounds for the problem. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
